  "justification": "This function is the internal workhorse called by the public pivot_table function for any non-list aggfunc (after splitting list-valued aggregation arguments into individual calls). It takes a DataFrame plus values, index, columns, a single aggfunc, fill_value, margins, dropna, margins_name, observed, sort, and kwargs. It: (1) validates value labels exist in data and filters to relevant columns; (2) groups data by concatenation of index+column keys and applies aggfunc; (3) if dropna, drops all-NaN rows; (4) if MultiIndex result, unstacks column-key levels to create 2D pivot layout with fill_value; (5) if not dropna, reindexes both axes against full Cartesian product of level values; (6) sorts columns if requested, fills NaN values, handles integer downcasting for len aggregations; (7) if margins, appends row/column totals via _add_margins; (8) cleans up by dropping redundant top-level column headers and transposing if no row index was specified."
